<item>
            <title>[LU-13513] osp_precreate_reserve() should not take d-&gt;opd_pre_status == -EIO as fatal</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13513</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When OST_CREATE (not resendable rpc) sent by precreate thread fails&lt;br/&gt;
    with network error, osp_pre_update_status() sets d-&amp;gt;opd_pre_status to&lt;br/&gt;
    EIO. osp_precreate_reserve() considers EIO as fatal and does not wait&lt;br/&gt;
    for another attempt from precreate thread. That may make&lt;br/&gt;
    mdt_intent_open to return ENOSPC confusing a caller.&lt;br/&gt;
    ENOSPC comes from lod_alloc_rr().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
